<item>
            <title>[LU-15508] Lnet IPv6 work exposed memory leak in GSS layer</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15508</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While testing a &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10391&quot; title=&quot;LNET: Support IPv6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10391&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10391&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch that touched LNetPrimaryNID() in the GSS code that patch was done incorrectly which lead to a failure path being exercised in the GSS layer that normally is not. The test failures showed an unknown memory leak which can be seen here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/gerrit-janitor/21309/testresults/runtests-ssk-ldiskfs-SSK-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/gerrit-janitor/21309/testresults/runtests-ssk-ldiskfs-SSK-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
