                            <comment id="325308" author="sebastien" created="Fri, 4 Feb 2022 16:12:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Memory leak was due to garbage written to &lt;tt&gt;/proc/net/rpc/auth.sptlrpc.init/channel&lt;/tt&gt; by &lt;tt&gt;lsvcgssd&lt;/tt&gt; daemon in case it was getting badly formatted auth data from kernel space (as it happened with incorrect patchset 8 or 9 of &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/43616&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/43616&lt;/a&gt;, because only kernel space format was changed).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
